# Project Knowledge Base: Medical Isotope Supply Optimizer

## Physics Constants
**Isotope**: Technetium-99m (Tc-99m)

*   **Half-life ($T_{1/2}$)**: 6.0 hours
*   **Decay Constant ($\lambda$)**:
    $$ \lambda = \frac{\ln(2)}{T_{1/2}} \approx \frac{0.693147}{6.0} \approx 0.115525 \text{ h}^{-1} $$

    *Usage*: Activity at time $t$ ($A_t$) given initial activity $A_0$:
    $$ A_t = A_0 e^{-\lambda t} $$

## Priority Tiers
Hospitals are categorized by tiers to prioritize supply, especially for regionally isolated areas.

| Tier Value | Category | Description | Proposed Weighting ($W_{tier}$) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **0** | Source | ANSTO Lucas Heights | N/A |
| **1** | Metro / Outer Metro | Standard urban access | 1.0 |
| **2** | Regional Hub / Coastal | Reduced access frequency | 2.0 |
| **3** | Remote / Border | Critical priority due to isolation | 4.0 |

*Note: Weights are proposed exponential ($2^{Tier-1}$) to strictly prioritize higher tiers in the objective function.*

